Let’s create a full Node.js project with a simple HTML front-end, so you can deploy it on your GCP VM

nodeapp/
 ├── public/
 │    └── index.html
 ├── app.js
 ├── package.json

Install Node.js & PM2

sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs npm -y
npm install -g pm2

cd /project/path
npm install

Start your Node.js app with PM2

pm2 start app.js --name nodeapp
pm2 save
pm2 startup
pm2 logs 

install and configure nginx as a reverse proxy 
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl restart nginx

/public/index.html   → frontend (UI)
/app.js              → backend (API)

Troubleshoot:
pm2 logs nodeapp - Check Logs
pm2 start app.js
pm2 status
